German

[edit]
German Wikipedia has an article on:
Syndrom
Wikipedia de

Etymology

[edit]

Learned borrowing from New Latin syndrome, from Ancient Greek συνδρομή (sundromḗ).

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): [zʏnˈdʁoːm]
  • Audio (Germany (Berlin)):(file)
  • Rhymes: -oːm

Noun

[edit]

Syndrom n (strong, genitive Syndroms, plural Syndrome)

  1. syndrome

Declension

[edit]
Declension of Syndrom [neuter, strong]
singular plural
indef. def. noun def. noun
nominative ein das Syndrom die Syndrome
genitive eines des Syndroms der Syndrome
dative einem dem Syndrom den Syndromen
accusative ein das Syndrom die Syndrome
